Question 2: Keywords Influencing Favorite Counts

(a) R Code:

# Load stop words
data(stop_words)

# Text preprocessing and keyword extraction
text_analysis <- data %>%
  select(text, favorite_count) %>%
  filter(favorite_count > 0) %>%  # Focus on tweets with favorites
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
  anti_join(stop_words, by = "word") %>%
  filter(!str_detect(word, "^[0-9]+$")) %>%  # Remove pure numbers
  filter(nchar(word) > 3)  # Remove short words

# Calculate average favorites per keyword
keyword_influence <- text_analysis %>%
  group_by(word) %>%
  summarise(
    avg_favorites = mean(favorite_count),
    tweet_count = n(),
    total_favorites = sum(favorite_count),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) %>%
  filter(tweet_count >= 10) %>%  # Minimum frequency threshold
  arrange(desc(avg_favorites))

print("Top 10 keywords by average favorite count:")

# Define categorization criteria based on text characteristics
data$text_category <- case_when(
  str_detect(data$text, "^RT @") ~ "Retweet",
  str_detect(data$text, "@[A-Za-z0-9_]+") ~ "Mention/Reply",
  str_detect(data$text, "http[s]?://") ~ "Link Share",
  str_detect(data$text, "[!]{2,}|[?]{2,}|[.]{3,}") ~ "Emotional/Emphasis",
  str_detect(data$text, "#[A-Za-z0-9_]+") ~ "Hashtag Content",
  TRUE ~ "Original Content"
)

# Analyze favorite counts by category
category_analysis <- data %>%
  group_by(text_category) %>%
  summarise(
    tweet_count = n(),

    max_favorites = max(favorite_count, na.rm = TRUE),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(avg_favorites)) %>%  # Remove NA categories

Question 5b: Spammer Detection

(a) R Code:

# Define spammer criteria
spammer_analysis <- data %>%
  group_by(user_screen_name) %>%
  summarise(
    tweet_count = n(),
    unique_days = n_distinct(tweet_date, na.rm = TRUE),
    tweets_per_day = tweet_count / pmax(unique_days, 1),
    avg_engagement = mean(favorite_count + retweet_count, na.rm = TRUE),
    duplicate_text_ratio = (n() - n_distinct(text)) / n(),
    retweet_ratio = sum(str_detect(text, "^RT @")) / n(),
    .groups = 'drop'
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    spammer_score = (tweets_per_day > 50) + 
                   (avg_engagement < 1) + 
                   (duplicate_text_ratio > 0.3) + 
                   (retweet_ratio > 0.8)
  ) %>%
  filter(spammer_score >= 2) %>%  # Users meeting 2+ spam criteria
  arrange(desc(tweets_per_day))

print("Potential spammers (score >= 2):")

Question 6: Sentiment Analysis and Engagement

(a) R Code:

# Get sentiment lexicon with error handling
tryCatch({
  nrc <- get_sentiments("nrc")
}, error = function(e) {
  cat("NRC lexicon not available, using basic sentiment approach\n")
  nrc <- data.frame(word = c("good", "bad", "great", "terrible", "amazing", "awful", "excellent", "horrible", "fantastic", "disappointing"), 
                   sentiment = c("positive", "negative", "positive", "negative", "positive", "negative", "positive", "negative", "positive", "negative"))
})

# Sentiment analysis for users
if(exists("nrc") && nrow(nrc) > 0) {
  sentiment_analysis <- data %>%
    select(user_screen_name, text) %>%
    unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
    inner_join(nrc, by = "word", relationship = "many-to-many") %>%
    filter(sentiment %in% c("positive", "negative")) %>%
    count(user_screen_name, sentiment) %>%
    pivot_wider(names_from = sentiment, values_from = n, values_fill = 0) %>%
    mutate(
      total_sentiment = positive + negative,
      negative_ratio = ifelse(total_sentiment > 0, negative / total_sentiment, 0)
    ) %>%
    filter(total_sentiment >= 20) %>%  # Minimum threshold for reliability
    arrange(desc(negative_ratio))

  print("Top 10 users by negative sentiment ratio:")
  print(head(sentiment_analysis, 10))
} else {
  cat("Sentiment analysis skipped due to lexicon unavailability\n")
}

Custom F1_Score Function

# Custom F1_Score function as specified
F1_Score <- function(y_true, y_pred, positive = NULL) {
  # Convert to factors if not already
  y_true <- as.factor(y_true)
  y_pred <- as.factor(y_pred)
  
  # Get the confusion matrix
  cm <- confusionMatrix(y_pred, y_true, positive = positive)
  
  # Return F1 score
  return(cm$byClass["F1"])
}

# ANOVA tests for faculty differences
faculty_anova_results <- data.frame(
  Feature = character(),
  F_statistic = numeric(),
  p_value = numeric(),
  stringsAsFactors = FALSE
)

for(feature in top_features) {
  tryCatch({
    formula_str <- paste(feature, "~ unit_faculty")
    aov_result <- aov(as.formula(formula_str), data = train_data)
    summary_aov <- summary(aov_result)
    
    faculty_anova_results <- rbind(faculty_anova_results, data.frame(
      Feature = feature,
      F_statistic = summary_aov[[1]]$`F value`[1],
      p_value = summary_aov[[1]]$`Pr(>F)`[1]
    ))
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Error with feature", feature, "\n")
  })
}

# T-tests for sex differences
sex_ttest_results <- data.frame(
  Feature = character(),
  t_statistic = numeric(),
  p_value = numeric(),
  stringsAsFactors = FALSE
)

# Filter data for t-tests
sex_data <- train_data %>%
  filter(!is.na(demographic_sex)) %>%
  filter(demographic_sex %in% names(sort(table(train_data$demographic_sex), decreasing = TRUE)[1:2]))

  tryCatch({
    if(nrow(sex_data) > 10 && length(unique(sex_data$demographic_sex)) == 2) {
      formula_str <- paste(feature, "~ demographic_sex")
      ttest_result <- t.test(as.formula(formula_str), data = sex_data)
      
      sex_ttest_results <- rbind(sex_ttest_results, data.frame(
        Feature = feature,
        t_statistic = ttest_result$statistic,
        p_value = ttest_result$p.value
      ))
    }
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Error with feature", feature, "\n")
  })
}

complete_train_rows <- complete.cases(X_train)
complete_val_rows <- complete.cases(X_val)

y_train <- y_train[complete_train_rows]

y_val <- y_val[complete_val_rows]

for(col in categorical_columns) {
  if(col %in% names(X_train) && col %in% names(X_val)) {

    X_train[[col]] <- factor(X_train[[col]], levels = train_levels)

# Method 1: Outlier treatment
detect_outliers <- function(x) {
  Q1 <- quantile(x, 0.25, na.rm = TRUE)
  Q3 <- quantile(x, 0.75, na.rm = TRUE)
  IQR <- Q3 - Q1
  lower <- Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
  upper <- Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
  return(x < lower | x > upper)
}

  summarise_all(~sum(detect_outliers(.), na.rm = TRUE)) %>%

    if(!all(is.na(feature_data)) &&

  complete_rows <- complete.cases(cor_data)
  
  if(sum(complete_rows) > 10) {
    cor_data_clean <- cor_data[complete_rows, , drop = FALSE]
    cor_matrix_full <- cor(cor_data_clean, use = "complete.obs")
    
    if(any(is.na(cor_matrix_full)) || any(is.infinite(cor_matrix_full))) {

        cat("Error in correlation filtering:", e$message, "\n")
